# m5_smoothing — host. Walks RIGHT for the entire match so the
# client sees a moving remote mech driven through the new P03
# two-snapshot interp buffer + alpha lerp render path.
#
# Pairs with m5_smoothing.client.shot which sits still and bursts
# screenshots over the host's walk. A working P03 implementation
# should show the host's mech moving smoothly across consecutive
# burst frames — no zigzag, no per-snapshot pop-back, no jitter.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/m5_smoothing_host
network host 24091
name HostA

# Start walking RIGHT shortly after match begin (~tick 130). Hold
# through the burst window so the client always sees lateral motion.
at 150 press right
at 150 shot start
at 400 shot mid
at 700 shot late
at 800 end
